name: Mariia  S.
headline: QA Engineer | Tester | Quality Assurance
creator: False
bio:
Ручной бэк-тестировщик в СовКомБанк Технологии. Лид команды бэк-тестирования из 14 человек.

Инструменты:
- БД (Redis, DBeaver(PostgreSQL, Oracle))
- Graylog (логи до уровня TRACE)
- YouTrack (ведение задач/багов)
- Pyrus, NextCloud, Outlook(для коммуникаций и отчётов)
- Confluence (анализ документации, работа с требованиями, написание командной документации)
- TestIT (тест-кейсы, регрессионные планы, запуск автотестов)
- Kafka (Kafkalytic in IntelliJ)
- Административная панель(внутренний инструмент работы с моками/конфигурациями/локалями (mocks/configuration/localization))
- QAD (внутренний инструмент для работы с нагрузочными тестами)
- Grafana (отслеживание метрик нагрузочного тестирования, состоянии тестовых стендов)
- DevTools (сбор методов/параметров для запросов)
- Postman (основной инструмент для тестирования задач)
- Android/iOS (Тестирование мобильного приложения: фронт с реальных устройств)

Для быстрой связи:
Почта vas9lisa.QA@gmail.com
Telegram https://t.me/vas9lisa

name: Ramin Afandiyev
headline: Full-Stack Software Engineer(React Native, React, Nodejs)
creator: False
bio:
Hi there! I'm Ramin Afandiyev, a skilled software engineer with experience in React Native, TypeScript, Node.js/Express, Django, and more.

In terms of programming languages, I am proficient in React Native, Expo, React, Mobx/Redux, Recoil, TypeScript, Node.js/Express, Django, Docker, Linux, Git, CI/CD, and SQL. I also have experience with end-to-end testing using Detox, and deploying to the Play Store and App Store using Codemagic CI/CD.

Aside from my technical skills, I possess strong soft skills such as teamwork, problem-solving, communication, time management, and adaptability. I have collaborated with various teams on different projects and have demonstrated the ability to work effectively under pressure and in fast-paced environments.

I am passionate about software development and constantly seek to learn and improve my skills. If you're looking for a software engineer who can help bring your ideas to life, I'd love to connect with you on LinkedIn.

I earned a Bachelor of Computer Science from UFAZ - French-Azerbaijan University. Through my studies, I have gained a strong foundation in software engineering principles and have developed skills in requirements engineering, personal software processing, analysis of software artifacts, architecture of software systems, and models of software systems.


Thanks for stopping by!

name: Viktar Karahoda
headline: Java Backend Developer, Kafka, RESTful WebServices, Web Services
creator: False
bio: As a Java Developer at Resliv, I applied my skills in Java Development, RESTful WebServices, and Web Services to create innovative solutions for various clients in different industries. I worked with a team of talented developers, designers, and testers to deliver high-quality products that met the client's requirements and expectations. I contributed to the design, development, testing, and deployment of multiple projects, using agile methodologies and best practices. I also supported the maintenance and enhancement of existing applications, as well as the troubleshooting and resolution of issues and bugs. I joined Resliv in August 2017, after working as a Java Software Engineer at BioSoftTraid for nine months, where I gained valuable experience in developing and testing web applications for the biotechnology sector. I have a bachelor's degree in Information Technology from Belarusian National Technical University, and I completed a Java Developer course at Innopolis University in 2017. I am passionate about learning new technologies and frameworks, and I am always eager to improve my skills and knowledge. I enjoy working in a collaborative and dynamic environment, where I can share my ideas and feedback with my colleagues and clients. I am looking for new opportunities and challenges that will allow me to leverage my expertise and grow as a professional.

bio:
Hi there!
I’m ISTQB Foundation Level-certified manual tester almost 2 years of experience and 2 years of technical supporting experience. I have a comprehensive knowledge of the project life-cycle and development processes. I'm very focused and strong motivated to achieve goals. I can only see my future in Tech.

Continuous improvement is essential to me, and I’m always looking for ways to enhance our processes and make things even better. I've been learning Python, and I even made my own pet project with a Telegram Bot. It was a fun and rewarding experience! I've uploaded the code to GitHub and my own server.

Let’s connect and see how I can bring my skills and enthusiasm to contribute to your organization’s success! Feel free to reach out. #QAEngineer #SoftwareTesting #QualityAssurance #SupportEngineer #Support #QA #Freelancer #Remote #Opentowork

Ready to work remote as a self-employed/freelancer from Germany or ready to relocate

Technologies:
Python, Devtools, Postman, Rest API, SQL, Kibana, TeamCity, GitHub, Selenium. 

My repo:
https://github.com/SADfranco

My telegram:
@andreishabaev

name: Ruslan Shakirov
headline: Managing Director at Heinrich Tapp Rus LLC
creator: False
bio:
Highly motivated and results-oriented business development leader with a proven track record of driving multi-million dollar sales and new business opportunities in the power generation and machine-building industries. Possesses exceptional expertise in managing complex projects and deals, with a keen ability to analyze market conditions and identify areas for growth. Proven success in:

Identifying and developing new business opportunities: Proactively identifies potential clients, distributors, and partners, builds strong relationships, and closes multi-million dollar sales deals.
Developing and implementing strategic sales plans: Creates and executes comprehensive sales and marketing strategies based on market potential, sales data, and growth projections.
Leading and managing high-performing teams: Provides effective leadership and guidance to teams, fostering a culture of collaboration and achieving ambitious goals.
Negotiating and closing complex contracts: Skilled negotiator with a strong understanding of contract terms and legal implications.
Building and maintaining strategic relationships: Cultivates and nurtures relationships with key decision-makers in the energy and oil & gas sectors, including top executives.
Providing pre- and post-sales support: Collaborates closely with technical and production teams to ensure client satisfaction and project success.
Overseeing advertising and promotional activities: Manages advertising campaigns and promotional initiatives to drive brand awareness and lead generation.
Improving competitive position: Identifies and analyzes market trends to stay ahead of the competition and adapt business strategies accordingly.
Project management: Coordinates and oversees the execution of complex projects, ensuring timely completion and adherence to budget constraints.
Key Qualifications:

Proven track record of exceeding sales targets and achieving significant revenue growth.
Strong analytical and strategic thinking skills.
Excellent communication, negotiation, and presentation skills.
Deep understanding of the power generation and machine-building industries.
Demonstrated ability to build and lead high-performing teams.
Strong relationship-building skills and experience working with key stakeholders.
Proven ability to manage complex projects and deliver results.

name: JOHN OKECHI
headline: Grant-Winning Business Manager | Strategic Project Manager | Visionary Product Designer | Web3 | Scaling Ideas Into Reality With No-Code & AI 🚀
creator: True
bio:
Let’s take a walk through my professional journey—one fueled by curiosity, resilience, and a drive to turn ideas into impactful solutions. 🌟

🎓 From Classroom to Innovation
With a Bachelor’s in Computer Science and Mathematics, a Master’s in IT Business Development, and a current PhD in Management, my career blends academic depth with hands-on experience.

🚀 From Python to Blockchain Mastery
Starting with Python, I explored sales, UX/UI design, and project management, eventually leading teams to secure two federal startup grants—Afro-Kiva in 2023 and Freshstart in 2024. Afro-Kiva, now MVP-ready, operates manually through social media while we navigate tax challenges in Russia.

🌐 Web3, No-Code & Crypto
My dive into Web3 includes managing NFT launches and building blockchain-powered solutions. Using tools like Bubble, Webflow, and AI, I create scalable platforms that bridge traditional processes with decentralized innovation.

✨ 
If you’re looking for a business developer, Web3 project manager, or no-code expert, let’s connect and build something extraordinary together!

👉 Check out my design portfolio at johnnytech.io

bio:

В данный момент изучаю NextJs. Работаю над проектом по поиску и агрегации публичных мероприятей в интересующем городе.

name: Maksim Al Dandan
headline: Java Software Engineer 😊 | Building Scalable & Resilient Systems 🚀 | Architecting Business-Critical Features 🔧 | Team Leadership & Collaboration 👥🔥
creator: False
bio:
Being passionate about backend development and scalable architectures, I thrive in designing robust, high-performance solutions that drive business efficiency 🚀.

At IT-One, I played a key role in a major banking project, taking full ownership of a core business feature for an upcoming release. This feature streamlines client operations, reducing manual effort and increasing overall efficiency. I have also worked on backend architecture improvements, ensuring the system can scale effectively as business demands grow. Tackling critical and high-impact issues, I have helped make the system more reliable and fault-tolerant, while refining the codebase with modern Java and Spring best practices to enhance development quality.

Beyond corporate development, I have taken ideas from concept to fully functional products. The Cardio Telegram Bot ❤️ was a full-cycle project where I designed, developed, and launched a fully operational system serving 800+ users. With a strong focus on automation and scalability, I integrated a CI/CD pipeline, making deployments faster and more efficient.

In the Restaurant Website project 🍴, I led a team of five developers, coordinating frontend and backend efforts while establishing an efficient Git workflow. This experience strengthened my teamwork, leadership, and mentoring skills, proving that successful projects are built through collaboration and technical excellence 👥🔥.

I’m always open to new challenges, exciting projects, and meaningful connections. Let’s build something amazing together! 😊💡🎯 You can reach out my CV in the Featured section.

name: Carlos Cano
headline: Cloud Application Architect @ AWS | DevOps | Tech Lead. Passionate about creating scalable solutions and leading tech teams. Let's connect and build amazing things together!
creator: False
bio:
Hi There! I'm Carlos Cano. With a passion for technology and creativity, I've developed a professional path that includes Cloud Architecture, Networking and DevOps. My journey has been motivated by a passion to create, develop, and lead teams to success in the fast-paced world of cloud computing.

As a Cloud Architect, I thrive on creating scalable, secure, and efficient cloud solutions that help organizations achieve their strategic goals. 

I've led many projects to move and modernize applications, making sure they use the latest technology. I really enjoy this work because it makes businesses run smoother and faster. 

For me, technology isn't just about gadgets and software; it's a key part of any business's success.

name: Anulika J. Nwankwo
headline: Software Product Designer (UX/UI) | Senior IT Product Manager
creator: True
current_position: Senior Product Manager & UX Design Lead
bio:
I studied for an intensive IT industry Masters degree in Computer Science majoring in Information Technology Entrepreneurship. I've been fortunate to be coached by IT entrepreneurs with Silicon Valley Experience, some of whom have been recognized on Forbes. I have vast experience in digital product development as a Product designer and Product Owner. 

I also obtained a Master of Science degree in Science, Technology and Innovation Management and Policy where I was trained by the best in cutting-edge innovation management experience that aligns with industry 4.0 principles, making me effective in Innovative Project Management, foresight studies to anticipate market trends and emerging technologies.

I have hands-on skills in overseeing Product lifecycles and scaling IT products, New product ideation and discovery, Product Vision alignment, Advanced Product Quality Planning, Analyzing Consumer Behaviour, Reviewing User feedback, Suggesting Product Improvements,  Industry Competitive Intelligence.

I also bring experience in creating user-centered solutions that meet business goals. I have a proven track record of working collaboratively with global cross-functional teams in product ideation, idea validation, market research, designing and launching successful products.

My approach is rooted in Agile methodology and Scrum, Design Thinking, Human Centered Computing and Data analytics, as I believe understanding the users (and their behaviour while using the product), the market and trend, are some of the foundations for creating effective solutions that appeal to a target audience who will use a specific product. I am passionate about data and details and I strive for excellence in every aspect of my work on I T product development, from the starting points of brainstorming, story boarding, persona development, qualitative and quantitative research, analyzing and prototyping to the final implementation.

I am a strong communicator and have experience presenting product solutions to stakeholders at all levels, internal and external. I value team collaboration and enjoy discussing ways to build better products for the changing market demands and  user needs.

As a Product Lead, I would like to help thousands of people every day and contribute to the social and digital inclusion of both the young and elderly by creating and shipping products that make a difference in people's lives while driving business success.

Get in touch: anuri.nwankwo@gmail.com
Book a meeting: https://calendly.com/anuri-nwankwo/30min

name: Vladimir Naumov
headline: HR Director
creator: False
bio:
A seasoned HR Leader with the Continuous Improvement mindset and experience of working in cross-boundaries projects with diverse international teams. 20+ years of working with various HR functions, including recruitment, talent assessment, development, and management, employees' coaching and training, executing the Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DEI) and engagement initiatives, delivering on complicated termination and business restructuring cases, and managing international teams of 20+ individuals (directors included).   

Delivered hundreds of leadership programs to senior audience around the Globe and trained thousands of participants in total. Certified as a corporate trainer/coach on multiple leadership classes, like "Situational Leadership (SLX II)" and "Coaching Essentials" by Ken Blanchard Group; "Crucial Conversations" by Vital Smarts; "Speed of Trust" by Franklin Covey, "Leadership Essentials" by Forum, "Building Inclusive Teams" by Hercules Coaching, and many other various programs on performance management, recruitment, relations building, and Diversity and Inclusion matters. 

Always strive to make the employer the best place to work for the teams and believe, that the only source of Company's development is its personnel.

name: Marat Fatkhullin
headline: Working in Europe, Russia, Africa, Middle Asia, Central Asia establishing international collaborations in science and health. Engagement with federal and regional governments, universities and funding agencies.
creator: False
school_1: Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology (State University) (MIPT)
bio:
Marat Fatkhullin works in Europe, Africa, Russia, Middle East and Central Asia establishing international collaborations in science and health.  He works with government ministers, regional governments, universities and funding agencies. Marat has worked with Elsevier since 2011 and is now Vice President of Global Strategic Networks

Marat has worked on many successful collaborative projects including: developing regional economies through evidence-based partnerships between industry and universities, advises universities transformation into entrepreneurial mode and facilitating the adoption of successful programmes to focus and improve research output quality.

Old years Background: "On Edge" FMCG Experience in Business Development, People Management and Trade Marketing converted into a real life Business Decisions in a new Industry with recognized Success and Volume Growth.

Searching for Executive Position in a result oriented Company that allow  self development by interesting challenging Objectives.

Desired (Dream) Spheres: Innovations, Pharmaceuticals, FMCG

Specialties: Adept at developing credibility and confidence with the public. Open minded. Operate well in a free, unstructured environment. Bring new life to conventional methods. A solid reputation for upholding high ethical standards and realizing corporate goals and objectives.

I am a creative person and I came into software development just as many others trying to figure out how to create my own video game and it went on and on from there, and here we are. I am a pacifist by nature, I love life and everything in it.

I do love starting things from scratch and learning from it, looking how different technologies work on the inside, natural curiosity.

Network programming is also in my area of interest. I have personal experience writing servers and multiplayer games, failed many times, but gained some knowledge.

name: Lev Berezhnoy
headline: Co-founder at MYRTEX | AI-Driven Solutions | Expert in Software Development and Process Management | Developer Proficient in Python, .NET Core C#, Angular, and SQL Databases
creator: False
bio:
I am an accomplished IT leader with over 10 years of experience in developing innovative and effective IT solutions and seamlessly integrating them into business processes. My expertise spans IT product development, process optimization, and team building, with a proven track record of solving complex problems, driving projects from concept to completion, and inspiring teams to exceed their objectives.

Key Achievements:
+ Co-Founder and CTO at MIRTEX: Developed a dynamic and scalable SaaS platform for grant management, growing the user base to over 400,000 and achieving an annual turnover of $8 million.
+ End-to-End Product Development: Led the full cycle of product development, from gathering requirements and coding the initial MVP to selecting the technology stack (.Net Core (C#), Angular TS, MS SQL, PostgreSQL, RabbitMQ, Redis, Elastic Stack, Docker), and collaborating with investors and early adopters.
+ Leadership in Uncertain Environments: Built and led a high-performing team of specialists, navigating a rapidly changing environment to deliver a successful IT product that met and exceeded market demands.

Core Competencies:
+ Technical Expertise: Advanced proficiency in Python, .Net Core (C#), Angular TS, MS SQL, PostgreSQL, RabbitMQ, Docker, and cloud platforms like Microsoft Azure.
+ Project Leadership: Skilled in overseeing end-to-end development processes, including requirements analysis, system architecture, implementation, testing, deployment, and ongoing support.
+ Team Building and Communication: Strong communicator with a talent for fostering collaboration, guiding teams, and aligning cross-functional efforts toward common goals.

My passion for integrating artificial intelligence into products and business processes has been further enhanced by my completion of a master's program in Artificial Intelligence. I am driven to leverage AI to create smarter, more efficient solutions that drive business value and innovation.

name: Рамзия Макарова
headline: Data Scientist | ML | CV | NLP | Python (t.me/Ramziya_Makarova)
creator: False
bio:
Создание продуктов по анализу данных полного цикла:
- настройка и осуществление парсинга данных (selenium, beautifulsoup),
- предобработка данных (разведочный анализ EDA, препроцессинг данных при помощи SQL и
Python);
- разработка архитектуры моделей для классификации и детекции изображений;
- подбор подходящих ML-моделей под поставленную аналитическую задачу, проведение
дообучения готовых моделей (классификация, регрессия, кластеризация, тренд и
прогнозирование во временных рядах ARIMA/SARIMA);
- оптимизация и "тюнинг" моделей (регуляризация, GridSearch, байесовская и градиентная
оптимизация, feature engineering);
- построение рекомендательных систем;
- перенос разработанных моделей на платформы streamlit и в клиентские чат-боты телеграм.
Примеры выполненных проектов:
- Проект для дилерского центра Toyota
(создание модели по расчету стоимости ремонта различной сложности для бамперов
автомобилей 13 марок по двум загруженным пользователем фотографиям в формате
клиентского чат-бота Телеграм. Подбор и разметка 8 000 фотографий, детекция - YOLO V5 от
Ultralytiks).
- Проект "What_kind_of_movie?"
(Рекомендательная модель, которая на основании описания фильма позволяет пользователю
увидеть названия кинолент, максимально подходящих под него. Парсинг с сайта Кинопоиск.ру
ТОП-250 фильмов. Написание модели на основании семантического сходства с точностью до
86%).
- Проект по визуализации данных по тренду медианной стоимости автомобилей по заданным
параметрам (марка, год выпуска, пробег,цвет кузова, объем двигателя) для внутреннего проекта "Middle Price" дилерского центра г.Алматы.

Стек: Python, Pandas, NumPy, SciPy, Scikit-learn, CatBoost, XGBoost, LightGBM, PyTorch, Matplotlib,
Seaborn, GoogleColab, Streamlit, Git, Bash, Docker, PostgreSQL, PyTorch, YOLO V5, Detectron2,
Roboflow, GoogleСolab, NLP, nltk, tf-idf

name: Oksana G.
headline: Diverse experience in Performance marketing & Creative producing│ BI analytics │ 10+ experience in Banking&Finance │ Google WTM Ambassador
creator: False
bio:
Hello, I am a technology enthusiast with a passion for launching new technologies to the market. 

I am fascinated by working in cross-functional teams and have gained experience in Marketing and Customer Success in both B2B and B2C environments. 

This has allowed me to focus on customers' needs and understand the product from the user's perspective when modeling customer experience and generating creative hypotheses based on customer insights.

name: Elizaveta Kolmakova
headline: Data Scientist at 1221Systems, DM telegram: @eksver
creator: False
bio:
Feel free to contact me via 
email: e.kolmakova@innopolis.university, 
or telegram: @eksver

Data scientist with experience in various domains, including CV, NLP, classic DS and recommender systems. I have extensive expertise in recommender systems and a deep understanding of how businesses can mitigate cold start issues, address popularity bias, and optimize key metrics through recommendation models and even more.

I have also worked extensively with NLP, tackling tasks such as product matching and customer support request classification in the absence of labeled datasets. My long-term goal is to fine-tune large language models (LLMs) to address both business and development needs.

Earlier:
- Extensive experience in projects related to healthcare and tabular data processing.
- Proficient in computer vision applications, though my primary focus lies elsewhere.
- Earned a master’s degree, with research focused on dataset balancing using GAN-based data generation.
- Fluent in English.

Most interested in projects in the field of NLP for the development of conversational AI systems or projects with the opportunity to gain experience in areas such as: voice assistant, virtual assistant, medical data processing. 
Also interested in application of Recommendation System approaches to various domains and big business.

bio:
I am an oil and gas business analyst in the development and implementation of industrial robotisation and 3D printing technologies. I have experience in supervising business analysis on key innovative software initiatives in the field of robotics and additive technologies, as well as developing and launching strategic projects in the company.
At the moment I am an employee of the Industry Competence Centre for Robotics, the implementation and functioning of which is the result of successful completion of a strategic project. In this Centre I am engaged in pre-project development and supervision of project activities, the purpose of which is to increase the level of robotisation density in industry in the Russian Federation. 
At the moment I am also a graduate student of the final course in the direction of "industrial safety in the mining industry".
In education I would like to mention successful completion of the international Master's programme at three joint universities (Russia, Germany, Austria), as well as successful completion of SQL courses at Innopolis University and acquisition of leadership and team management skills at the corresponding course at Netology.

headline: Senior Product Manager | Leading Internal Comms Platform @ T-Bank | MSc in Software Engineering
creator: False
bio:
As a product manager with 10 years of experience and a master’s degree in Software Development Management, I combine strategic vision with hands-on execution. I specialize in building internal tech platforms and complex, user-focused solutions that make a real difference — for organizations and for people.

What makes me different?
- A solid foundation in IT management from Innopolis University (Carnegie Mellon-based).
- First-hand experience launching startups inside large corporations.
- Passion for user-centered design — I believe internal tools should be as intuitive and delightful as consumer-facing ones.
- Empathy-driven leadership — I build trust, motivate teams, and create space for people to thrive.

I love turning messy, complex problems into clear, elegant systems. Whether it’s scaling platforms for 120,000+ users or running a 100-team hackathon — I bring structure, energy, and focus. My leadership style is about enabling others to do their best work — with clarity, care, and a shared sense of purpose.

creator: False
bio:
I am a skilled engineer with extensive experience in mobile development, driver development, and technical projects. My passion lies in harnessing technology to solve complex challenges and create innovative solutions.

With a solid foundation in programming languages and technologies—including C, C++, Dart, Flutter, Python, and Java—I have a proven track record in diverse areas such as API development, encryption, and network protocols. My technical expertise extends to CI/CD processes, SQL Server, and Linux, among others.

Some of my most significant projects include:

    Developing a smart contract language that enhances blockchain interactions.
    Creating peer-to-peer network protocols that improve communication and data sharing.
    Building a card payment system for Russia's MIR Payment system, driving advancements in financial technology.

I thrive in collaborative environments where I can share ideas and push the boundaries of what's possible. Let’s connect and explore opportunities to innovate together!

bio:
I'm a dedicated Quality Assurance professional with a focus on ensuring user experiences in software applications. I believe in assessing applications through a user's perspective and emphasize the importance of quality in every project. I prefer to  communicate precisely, it allows me to accurately estimate project timelines and identify potential risks. I take responsibility not only for my personal work but also for my team's results.

My attention to detail and commitment to high standards make me a professional in my work. I'm genuinely passionate about my profession and aim to make a meaningful impact in the field of quality assurance.

My professional background includes expertise in building QA processes from scratch, managing QA teams, recruiting and training quality assurance engineers, and implementing testing automation. In my free time, I'm dedicated to improving my English skills and continuously expanding my knowledge of soft skills. I also enjoy digital illustration as a hobby.

My career aspirations include influencing the final product, advancing within the quality assurance field, and being an integral part of a team that values and prioritizes quality in its work. If you'd like to connect or discuss potential collaborations, please feel free to reach out on Telegram at https://t.me/Leontyeva.

I'm open to connecting with professionals who share a passion for quality and a user-centered approach in the tech industry. Let's connect and explore potential opportunities to collaborate on interesting projects.

Thanks!

name: Maria Zykova
headline: Data Analyst
creator: False
bio:
Hi!

I am interested in data analysis and artificial intelligence and follow the development and expansion of skills.

I have experience working on projects on analyzing customer data for recommendation systems and predicting customer behavior, I also developed time series forecasting models and assessed the risk of a stock portfolio, analyzed text data and tried out various machine learning and neural network methods.

I participated in such competitions as the Arctic Technology Competition and Yandex Cup 2023 RecSys.

I play sports, participate in team and individual running, and explore creativity through music, theater, and painting. I am in love with fiction and detective stories in the world of literature.

You can view my projects in my github profile by clicking on the link in the Favorites section.
